  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "<!-- Please only use this template for submitting enhancement requests -->\r\n\r\n**What would you like to be added**:\r\n\r\nCurrently, when AAD login is configured, refresh token timeout would make kubectl print an error, not able to re-login without manually remove the tokens. Expect kubectl to promote user to login again.\r\n\r\n**Why is this needed**:\r\n\r\nConfigure refresh-token timeout from Azure is a way to force re-login after inactivity. kubectl doesn't promote re-login makes users harder to apply timeout policy.\r\n",
